{
  "video_id": "CDdpQSLr7YE",
  "title": "A new way to study the brain's invisible secrets | Ed Boyden",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12904.0,
      "end_time": 14333.0,
      "text": "Hello, everybody."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14333.0,
      "end_time": 18793.0,
      "text": "I brought with me today a baby diaper."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18793.0,
      "end_time": 20539.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ll see why in a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20539.0,
      "end_time": 22573.0,
      "text": "Baby diapers have interesting properties."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22573.0,
      "end_time": 25288.0,
      "text": "They can swell enormously when you add water to them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25288.0,
      "end_time": 28296.0,
      "text": "an experiment done by millions of kids every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28296.0,
      "end_time": 29470.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 29470.0,
      "end_time": 30988.0,
      "text": "But the reason why"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 30988.0,
      "end_time": 33202.0,
      "text": "is that they&#39;re designed in a very clever way."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 33202.0,
      "end_time": 35861.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re made out of a thing called a swellable material."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 35861.0,
      "end_time": 38622.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a special kind of material that, when you add water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 38622.0,
      "end_time": 40076.0,
      "text": "it will swell up enormously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 40076.0,
      "end_time": 42266.0,
      "text": "maybe a thousand times in volume."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 42266.0,
      "end_time": 45819.0,
      "text": "And this is a very useful, industrial kind of polymer."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 45819.0,
      "end_time": 48369.0,
      "text": "But what we&#39;re trying to do in my group at MIT"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 48369.0,
      "end_time": 51606.0,
      "text": "is to figure out if we can do something similar to the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 51606.0,
      "end_time": 52789.0,
      "text": "Can we make it bigger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 52789.0,
      "end_time": 54481.0,
      "text": "big enough that you can peer inside"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 54481.0,
      "end_time": 57133.0,
      "text": "and see all the tiny building blocks, the biomolecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 57133.0,
      "end_time": 59308.0,
      "text": "how they&#39;re organized in three dimensions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 59308.0,
      "end_time": 62817.0,
      "text": "the structure, the ground truth structure of the brain, if you will?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 62817.0,
      "end_time": 63999.0,
      "text": "If we could get that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 63999.0,
      "end_time": 67532.0,
      "text": "maybe we could have a better understanding of how the brain is organized"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 67532.0,
      "end_time": 69215.0,
      "text": "to yield thoughts and emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 69215.0,
      "end_time": 70958.0,
      "text": "and actions and sensations."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 70958.0,
      "end_time": 74397.0,
      "text": "Maybe we could try to pinpoint the exact changes in the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74397.0,
      "end_time": 76197.0,
      "text": "that result in diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 76197.0,
      "end_time": 79433.0,
      "text": "diseases like Alzheimer&#39;s and epilepsy and Parkinson&#39;s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 79433.0,
      "end_time": 82035.0,
      "text": "for which there are few treatments, much less cures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 82035.0,
      "end_time": 85676.0,
      "text": "and for which, very often, we don&#39;t know the cause or the origins"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 85676.0,
      "end_time": 88613.0,
      "text": "and what&#39;s really causing them to occur."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88613.0,
      "end_time": 90377.0,
      "text": "Now, our group at MIT"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 90377.0,
      "end_time": 93087.0,
      "text": "is trying to take a different point of view"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 93087.0,
      "end_time": 96341.0,
      "text": "from the way neuroscience has been done over the last hundred years."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 96341.0,
      "end_time": 97944.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re designers. We&#39;re inventors."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 97944.0,
      "end_time": 100512.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re trying to figure out how to build technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 100512.0,
      "end_time": 102992.0,
      "text": "that let us look at and repair the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 102992.0,
      "end_time": 104167.0,
      "text": "And the reason is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 104167.0,
      "end_time": 107484.0,
      "text": "the brain is incredibly, incredibly complicated."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 107484.0,
      "end_time": 110395.0,
      "text": "So what we&#39;ve learned over the first century of neuroscience"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 110395.0,
      "end_time": 112722.0,
      "text": "is that the brain is a very complicated network,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 112722.0,
      "end_time": 115226.0,
      "text": "made out of very specialized cells called neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 115226.0,
      "end_time": 116917.0,
      "text": "with very complex geometries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 116917.0,
      "end_time": 121653.0,
      "text": "and electrical currents will flow through these complexly shaped neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 121653.0,
      "end_time": 124461.0,
      "text": "Furthermore, neurons are connected in networks."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 124461.0,
      "end_time": 128320.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re connected by little junctions called synapses that exchange chemicals"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 128320.0,
      "end_time": 130562.0,
      "text": "and allow the neurons to talk to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 130562.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132526.0,
      "text": "The density of the brain is incredible."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 132526.0,
      "end_time": 134857.0,
      "text": "In a cubic millimeter of your brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 134857.0,
      "end_time": 137338.0,
      "text": "there are about 100,000 of these neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 137338.0,
      "end_time": 140887.0,
      "text": "and maybe a billion of those connections."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 140887.0,
      "end_time": 142293.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s worse."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 142293.0,
      "end_time": 144622.0,
      "text": "So, if you could zoom in to a neuron,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 144622.0,
      "end_time": 147396.0,
      "text": "and, of course, this is just our artist&#39;s rendition of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 147396.0,
      "end_time": 151627.0,
      "text": "What you would see are thousands and thousands of kinds of biomolecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 151627.0,
      "end_time": 156051.0,
      "text": "little nanoscale machines organized in complex, 3D patterns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 156051.0,
      "end_time": 158703.0,
      "text": "and together they mediate those electrical pulses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 158703.0,
      "end_time": 162664.0,
      "text": "those chemical exchanges that allow neurons to work together"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 162664.0,
      "end_time": 166357.0,
      "text": "to generate things like thoughts and feelings and so forth."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 166357.0,
      "end_time": 170145.0,
      "text": "Now, we don&#39;t know how the neurons in the brain are organized"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 170145.0,
      "end_time": 171343.0,
      "text": "to form networks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 171343.0,
      "end_time": 173867.0,
      "text": "and we don&#39;t know how the biomolecules are organized"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 173867.0,
      "end_time": 175065.0,
      "text": "within neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 175065.0,
      "end_time": 177918.0,
      "text": "to form these complex, organized machines."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 177918.0,
      "end_time": 179762.0,
      "text": "If we really want to understand this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 179762.0,
      "end_time": 181603.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to need new technologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 181603.0,
      "end_time": 183411.0,
      "text": "But if we could get such maps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 183411.0,
      "end_time": 186378.0,
      "text": "if we could look at the organization of molecules and neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 186378.0,
      "end_time": 187968.0,
      "text": "and neurons and networks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 187968.0,
      "end_time": 191429.0,
      "text": "maybe we could really understand how the brain conducts information"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 191429.0,
      "end_time": 192620.0,
      "text": "from sensory regions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 192620.0,
      "end_time": 194380.0,
      "text": "mixes it with emotion and feeling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 194380.0,
      "end_time": 197131.0,
      "text": "and generates our decisions and actions."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 197131.0,
      "end_time": 200944.0,
      "text": "Maybe we could pinpoint the exact set of molecular changes that occur"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 200944.0,
      "end_time": 202170.0,
      "text": "in a brain disorder."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 202170.0,
      "end_time": 205016.0,
      "text": "And once we know how those molecules have changed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 205016.0,
      "end_time": 207820.0,
      "text": "whether they&#39;ve increased in number or changed in pattern,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 207820.0,
      "end_time": 210783.0,
      "text": "we could use those as targets for new drugs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 210783.0,
      "end_time": 213078.0,
      "text": "for new ways of delivering energy into the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 213078.0,
      "end_time": 216982.0,
      "text": "in order to repair the brain computations that are afflicted"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 216982.0,
      "end_time": 219793.0,
      "text": "in patients who suffer from brain disorders."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 219793.0,
      "end_time": 223060.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve all seen lots of different technologies over the last century"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 223060.0,
      "end_time": 224250.0,
      "text": "to try to confront this."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 224250.0,
      "end_time": 226154.0,
      "text": "I think we&#39;ve all seen brain scans"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 226154.0,
      "end_time": 228212.0,
      "text": "taken using MRI machines."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 228212.0,
      "end_time": 231583.0,
      "text": "These, of course, have the great power that they are noninvasive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 231583.0,
      "end_time": 234407.0,
      "text": "they can be used on living human subjects."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 234407.0,
      "end_time": 236662.0,
      "text": "But also, they&#39;re spatially crude."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 236662.0,
      "end_time": 239676.0,
      "text": "Each of these blobs that you see, or voxels, as they&#39;re called,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 239676.0,
      "end_time": 242389.0,
      "text": "can contain millions and millions of neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 242389.0,
      "end_time": 244263.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s not at the level of resolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 244263.0,
      "end_time": 246825.0,
      "text": "where it can pinpoint the molecular changes that occur"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 246825.0,
      "end_time": 249135.0,
      "text": "or the changes in the wiring of these networks"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 249135.0,
      "end_time": 253797.0,
      "text": "that contributes to our ability to be conscious and powerful beings."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 253797.0,
      "end_time": 257002.0,
      "text": "At the other extreme, you have microscopes."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 257002.0,
      "end_time": 260321.0,
      "text": "Microscopes, of course, will use light to look at little tiny things."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 260321.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263420.0,
      "text": "For centuries, they&#39;ve been used to look at things like bacteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 263420.0,
      "end_time": 264595.0,
      "text": "For neuroscience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 264595.0,
      "end_time": 268031.0,
      "text": "microscopes are actually how neurons were discovered in the first place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 268031.0,
      "end_time": 269347.0,
      "text": "about 130 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 269347.0,
      "end_time": 271689.0,
      "text": "But light is fundamentally limited."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 271689.0,
      "end_time": 275011.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t see individual molecules with a regular old microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 275011.0,
      "end_time": 277187.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t look at these tiny connections."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 277187.0,
      "end_time": 281153.0,
      "text": "So if we want to make our ability to see the brain more powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 281153.0,
      "end_time": 283345.0,
      "text": "to get down to the ground truth structure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 283345.0,
      "end_time": 287611.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to need to have even better technologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 287611.0,
      "end_time": 289859.0,
      "text": "My group, a couple years ago, started thinking:"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 289859.0,
      "end_time": 291295.0,
      "text": "Why don&#39;t we do the opposite?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 291295.0,
      "end_time": 293780.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s so darn complicated to zoom in to the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 293780.0,
      "end_time": 296166.0,
      "text": "why can&#39;t we make the brain bigger?"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 296166.0,
      "end_time": 297345.0,
      "text": "It initially started"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 297345.0,
      "end_time": 300365.0,
      "text": "with two grad students in my group, Fei Chen and Paul Tillberg."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 300365.0,
      "end_time": 303109.0,
      "text": "Now many others in my group are helping with this process."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 303109.0,
      "end_time": 305895.0,
      "text": "We decided to try to figure out if we could take polymers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 305895.0,
      "end_time": 307548.0,
      "text": "like the stuff in the baby diaper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 307548.0,
      "end_time": 309578.0,
      "text": "and install it physically within the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 309578.0,
      "end_time": 311843.0,
      "text": "If we could do it just right, and you add water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 311843.0,
      "end_time": 313702.0,
      "text": "you can potentially blow the brain up"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 313702.0,
      "end_time": 317103.0,
      "text": "to where you could distinguish those tiny biomolecules from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 317103.0,
      "end_time": 319997.0,
      "text": "You would see those connections and get maps of the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 319997.0,
      "end_time": 322009.0,
      "text": "This could potentially be quite dramatic."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 322009.0,
      "end_time": 325538.0,
      "text": "We brought a little demo here."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 325538.0,
      "end_time": 328137.0,
      "text": "We got some purified baby diaper material."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 328137.0,
      "end_time": 330435.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s much easier just to buy it off the Internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 330435.0,
      "end_time": 333934.0,
      "text": "than to extract the few grains that actually occur in these diapers."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 333934.0,
      "end_time": 336706.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to put just one teaspoon here"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 336706.0,
      "end_time": 339270.0,
      "text": "of this purified polymer."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 339270.0,
      "end_time": 341446.0,
      "text": "And here we have some water."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 341446.0,
      "end_time": 342632.0,
      "text": "What we&#39;re going to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 342632.0,
      "end_time": 345667.0,
      "text": "is see if this teaspoon of the baby diaper material"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 345667.0,
      "end_time": 348687.0,
      "text": "can increase in size."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 348687.0,
      "end_time": 352407.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re going to see it increase in volume by about a thousandfold"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 352407.0,
      "end_time": 361597.0,
      "text": "before your very eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 361597.0,
      "end_time": 363593.0,
      "text": "I could pour much more of this in there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 363593.0,
      "end_time": 365175.0,
      "text": "but I think you&#39;ve got the idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 365175.0,
      "end_time": 367701.0,
      "text": "that this is a very, very interesting molecule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 367701.0,
      "end_time": 369637.0,
      "text": "and if can use it in the right way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 369637.0,
      "end_time": 371982.0,
      "text": "we might be able to really zoom in on the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 371982.0,
      "end_time": 375227.0,
      "text": "in a way that you can&#39;t do with past technologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 375227.0,
      "end_time": 377305.0,
      "text": "OK. So a little bit of chemistry now."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 377305.0,
      "end_time": 379771.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s going on in the baby diaper polymer?"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 379771.0,
      "end_time": 381471.0,
      "text": "If you could zoom in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 381471.0,
      "end_time": 384168.0,
      "text": "it might look something like what you see on the screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 384168.0,
      "end_time": 388684.0,
      "text": "Polymers are chains of atoms arranged in long, thin lines."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 388684.0,
      "end_time": 390075.0,
      "text": "The chains are very tiny,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 390075.0,
      "end_time": 391963.0,
      "text": "about the width of a biomolecule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 391963.0,
      "end_time": 393734.0,
      "text": "and these polymers are really dense."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 393734.0,
      "end_time": 395258.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re separated by distances"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 395258.0,
      "end_time": 397534.0,
      "text": "that are around the size of a biomolecule."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 397534.0,
      "end_time": 398723.0,
      "text": "This is very good"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 398723.0,
      "end_time": 401788.0,
      "text": "because we could potentially move everything apart in the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 401788.0,
      "end_time": 403660.0,
      "text": "If we add water, what will happen is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 403660.0,
      "end_time": 406199.0,
      "text": "this swellable material is going to absorb the water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 406199.0,
      "end_time": 408623.0,
      "text": "the polymer chains will move apart from each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 408623.0,
      "end_time": 411615.0,
      "text": "and the entire material is going to become bigger."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 411615.0,
      "end_time": 413453.0,
      "text": "And because these chains are so tiny"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 413453.0,
      "end_time": 415682.0,
      "text": "and spaced by biomolecular distances,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 415682.0,
      "end_time": 417745.0,
      "text": "we could potentially blow up the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 417745.0,
      "end_time": 420020.0,
      "text": "and make it big enough to see."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 420020.0,
      "end_time": 421284.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the mystery, then:"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 421284.0,
      "end_time": 424918.0,
      "text": "How do we actually make these polymer chains inside the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 424918.0,
      "end_time": 427181.0,
      "text": "so we can move all the biomolecules apart?"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 427181.0,
      "end_time": 428356.0,
      "text": "If we could do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 428356.0,
      "end_time": 430777.0,
      "text": "maybe we could get ground truth maps of the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 430777.0,
      "end_time": 432190.0,
      "text": "We could look at the wiring."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 432190.0,
      "end_time": 435925.0,
      "text": "We can peer inside and see the molecules within."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 435925.0,
      "end_time": 438430.0,
      "text": "To explain this, we made some animations"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 438430.0,
      "end_time": 441057.0,
      "text": "where we actually look at, in these artist renderings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 441057.0,
      "end_time": 444622.0,
      "text": "what biomolecules might look like and how we might separate them."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 444622.0,
      "end_time": 447195.0,
      "text": "Step one: what we&#39;d have to do, first of all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 447195.0,
      "end_time": 450608.0,
      "text": "is attach every biomolecule, shown in brown here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 450608.0,
      "end_time": 452791.0,
      "text": "to a little anchor, a little handle."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 452791.0,
      "end_time": 455910.0,
      "text": "We need to pull the molecules of the brain apart from each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 455910.0,
      "end_time": 458260.0,
      "text": "and to do that, we need to have a little handle"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 458260.0,
      "end_time": 460569.0,
      "text": "that allows those polymers to bind to them"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 460569.0,
      "end_time": 463278.0,
      "text": "and to exert their force."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 463278.0,
      "end_time": 466463.0,
      "text": "Now, if you just take baby diaper polymer and dump it on the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 466463.0,
      "end_time": 468524.0,
      "text": "obviously, it&#39;s going to sit there on top."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 468524.0,
      "end_time": 471076.0,
      "text": "So we need to find a way to make the polymers inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 471076.0,
      "end_time": 472888.0,
      "text": "And this is where we&#39;re really lucky."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 472888.0,
      "end_time": 475100.0,
      "text": "It turns out, you can get the building blocks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 475100.0,
      "end_time": 476496.0,
      "text": "monomers, as they&#39;re called,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 476496.0,
      "end_time": 478304.0,
      "text": "and if you let them go into the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 478304.0,
      "end_time": 480364.0,
      "text": "and then trigger the chemical reactions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 480364.0,
      "end_time": 483090.0,
      "text": "you can get them to form those long chains,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 483090.0,
      "end_time": 485325.0,
      "text": "right there inside the brain tissue."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 485325.0,
      "end_time": 487746.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re going to wind their way around biomolecules"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 487746.0,
      "end_time": 488991.0,
      "text": "and between biomolecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 488991.0,
      "end_time": 490640.0,
      "text": "forming those complex webs"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 490640.0,
      "end_time": 493526.0,
      "text": "that will allow you, eventually, to pull apart the molecules"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 493526.0,
      "end_time": 494725.0,
      "text": "from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 494725.0,
      "end_time": 497803.0,
      "text": "And every time one of those little handles is around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 497803.0,
      "end_time": 501177.0,
      "text": "the polymer will bind to the handle, and that&#39;s exactly what we need"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 501177.0,
      "end_time": 503732.0,
      "text": "in order to pull the molecules apart from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 503732.0,
      "end_time": 505449.0,
      "text": "All right, the moment of truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 505449.0,
      "end_time": 507621.0,
      "text": "We have to treat this specimen"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 507621.0,
      "end_time": 511091.0,
      "text": "with a chemical to kind of loosen up all the molecules from each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 511091.0,
      "end_time": 512951.0,
      "text": "and then, when we add water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 512951.0,
      "end_time": 515928.0,
      "text": "that swellable material is going to start absorbing the water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 515928.0,
      "end_time": 517655.0,
      "text": "the polymer chains will move apart,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 517655.0,
      "end_time": 520401.0,
      "text": "but now, the biomolecules will come along for the ride."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 520400.99999999994,
      "end_time": 522588.99999999994,
      "text": "And much like drawing a picture on a balloon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 522589.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524200.00000000006,
      "text": "and then you blow up the balloon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 524200.00000000006,
      "end_time": 525514.0,
      "text": "the image is the same,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 525514.0,
      "end_time": 528086.0,
      "text": "but the ink particles have moved away from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 528086.0,
      "end_time": 531577.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s what we&#39;ve been able to do now, but in three dimensions."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 531577.0,
      "end_time": 533600.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s one last trick."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 533600.0,
      "end_time": 534842.0,
      "text": "As you can see here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 534842.0,
      "end_time": 536975.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve color-coded all the biomolecules brown."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 536975.0,
      "end_time": 539169.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s because they all kind of look the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 539169.0,
      "end_time": 541298.0,
      "text": "Biomolecules are made out of the same atoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 541298.0,
      "end_time": 543562.0,
      "text": "but just in different orders."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 543562.0,
      "end_time": 545086.0,
      "text": "So we need one last thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 545086.0,
      "end_time": 546805.0,
      "text": "in order to make them visible."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 546805.0,
      "end_time": 548408.0,
      "text": "We have to bring in little tags,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 548408.0,
      "end_time": 551451.0,
      "text": "with glowing dyes that will distinguish them."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 551451.0,
      "end_time": 554148.0,
      "text": "So one kind of biomolecule might get a blue color."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 554148.0,
      "end_time": 556523.0,
      "text": "Another kind of biomolecule might get a red color."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 556523.0,
      "end_time": 557823.0,
      "text": "And so forth."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 557823.0,
      "end_time": 559399.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the final step."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 559399.0,
      "end_time": 561701.0,
      "text": "Now we can look at something like a brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 561701.0,
      "end_time": 563521.0,
      "text": "and look at the individual molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 563521.0,
      "end_time": 566252.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;ve moved them far apart enough from each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 566252.0,
      "end_time": 567974.0,
      "text": "that we can tell them apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 567974.0,
      "end_time": 570832.0,
      "text": "So the hope here is that we can make the invisible visible."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 570832.0,
      "end_time": 573422.0,
      "text": "We can turn things that might seem small and obscure"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 573422.0,
      "end_time": 574597.0,
      "text": "and blow them up"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 574597.0,
      "end_time": 577798.0,
      "text": "until they&#39;re like constellations of information about life."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 577798.0,
      "end_time": 580197.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an actual video of what it might look like."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 580197.0,
      "end_time": 582592.0,
      "text": "We have here a little brain in a dish --"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 582592.0,
      "end_time": 584363.0,
      "text": "a little piece of a brain, actually."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 584363.0,
      "end_time": 585983.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve infused the polymer in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 585983.0,
      "end_time": 587474.0,
      "text": "and now we&#39;re adding water."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 587474.0,
      "end_time": 589856.0,
      "text": "What you&#39;ll see is that, right before your eyes --"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 589856.0,
      "end_time": 591803.0,
      "text": "this video is sped up about sixtyfold --"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 591803.0,
      "end_time": 594552.0,
      "text": "this little piece of brain tissue is going to grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 594552.0,
      "end_time": 597756.0,
      "text": "It can increase by a hundredfold or even more in volume."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 597756.0,
      "end_time": 600729.0,
      "text": "And the cool part is, because those polymers are so tiny,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 600729.0,
      "end_time": 603312.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re separating biomolecules evenly from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 603312.0,
      "end_time": 604994.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a smooth expansion."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 604994.0,
      "end_time": 607705.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re not losing the configuration of the information."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 607705.0,
      "end_time": 611333.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re just making it easier to see."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 611333.0,
      "end_time": 613533.0,
      "text": "So now we can take actual brain circuitry --"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 613533.0,
      "end_time": 616691.0,
      "text": "here&#39;s a piece of the brain involved with, for example, memory --"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 616691.0,
      "end_time": 617978.0,
      "text": "and we can zoom in."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 617978.0,
      "end_time": 620892.0,
      "text": "We can start to actually look at how circuits are configured."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 620892.0,
      "end_time": 622884.0,
      "text": "Maybe someday we could read out a memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 622884.0,
      "end_time": 625687.0,
      "text": "Maybe we could actually look at how circuits are configured"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 625687.0,
      "end_time": 626863.0,
      "text": "to process emotions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 626863.0,
      "end_time": 629809.0,
      "text": "how the actual wiring of our brain is organized"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 629809.0,
      "end_time": 632400.0,
      "text": "in order to make us who we are."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 632400.0,
      "end_time": 634471.0,
      "text": "And of course, we can pinpoint, hopefully,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 634471.0,
      "end_time": 637654.0,
      "text": "the actual problems in the brain at a molecular level."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 637654.0,
      "end_time": 640247.0,
      "text": "What if we could actually look into cells in the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 640247.0,
      "end_time": 643354.0,
      "text": "and figure out, wow, here are the 17 molecules that have altered"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 643354.0,
      "end_time": 646833.0,
      "text": "in this brain tissue that has been undergoing epilepsy"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 646833.0,
      "end_time": 648507.0,
      "text": "or changing in Parkinson&#39;s disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 648507.0,
      "end_time": 650048.0,
      "text": "or otherwise being altered?"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 650048.0,
      "end_time": 653115.0,
      "text": "If we get that systematic list of things that are going wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 653115.0,
      "end_time": 655338.0,
      "text": "those become our therapeutic targets."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 655338.0,
      "end_time": 657039.0,
      "text": "We can build drugs that bind those."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 657039.0,
      "end_time": 659690.0,
      "text": "We can maybe aim energy at different parts of the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 659690.0,
      "end_time": 662401.0,
      "text": "in order to help people with Parkinson&#39;s or epilepsy"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 662401.0,
      "end_time": 664976.0,
      "text": "or other conditions that affect over a billion people"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 664976.0,
      "end_time": 667246.0,
      "text": "around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 667246.0,
      "end_time": 669476.0,
      "text": "Now, something interesting has been happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 669476.0,
      "end_time": 672205.0,
      "text": "It turns out that throughout biomedicine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 672205.0,
      "end_time": 674895.0,
      "text": "there are other problems that expansion might help with."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 674895.0,
      "end_time": 678505.0,
      "text": "This is an actual biopsy from a human breast cancer patient."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 678505.0,
      "end_time": 680717.0,
      "text": "It turns out that if you look at cancers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 680717.0,
      "end_time": 682352.0,
      "text": "if you look at the immune system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 682352.0,
      "end_time": 684889.0,
      "text": "if you look at aging, if you look at development --"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 684889.0,
      "end_time": 689410.0,
      "text": "all these processes are involving large-scale biological systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 689410.0,
      "end_time": 693458.0,
      "text": "But of course, the problems begin with those little nanoscale molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 693458.0,
      "end_time": 697351.0,
      "text": "the machines that make the cells and the organs in our body tick."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 697351.0,
      "end_time": 699597.0,
      "text": "So what we&#39;re trying to do now is to figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 699597.0,
      "end_time": 703087.0,
      "text": "if we can actually use this technology to map the building blocks of life"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 703087.0,
      "end_time": 704856.0,
      "text": "in a wide variety of diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 704856.0,
      "end_time": 707776.0,
      "text": "Can we actually pinpoint the molecular changes in a tumor"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 707776.0,
      "end_time": 710169.0,
      "text": "so that we can actually go after it in a smart way"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 710169.0,
      "end_time": 714137.0,
      "text": "and deliver drugs that might wipe out exactly the cells that we want to?"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 714137.0,
      "end_time": 716496.0,
      "text": "You know, a lot of medicine is very high risk."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 716496.0,
      "end_time": 718626.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, it&#39;s even guesswork."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 718626.0,
      "end_time": 722525.0,
      "text": "My hope is we can actually turn what might be a high-risk moon shot"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 722525.0,
      "end_time": 724318.0,
      "text": "into something that&#39;s more reliable."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 724318.0,
      "end_time": 726397.0,
      "text": "If you think about the original moon shot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 726397.0,
      "end_time": 728319.0,
      "text": "where they actually landed on the moon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 728319.0,
      "end_time": 729787.0,
      "text": "it was based on solid science."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 729787.0,
      "end_time": 731414.0,
      "text": "We understood gravity;"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 731414.0,
      "end_time": 732779.0,
      "text": "we understood aerodynamics."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 732779.0,
      "end_time": 734198.0,
      "text": "We knew how to build rockets."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 734198.0,
      "end_time": 736690.0,
      "text": "The science risk was under control."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 736690.0,
      "end_time": 739467.0,
      "text": "It was still a great, great feat of engineering."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 739467.0,
      "end_time": 742136.0,
      "text": "But in medicine, we don&#39;t necessarily have all the laws."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 742136.0,
      "end_time": 745269.0,
      "text": "Do we have all the laws that are analogous to gravity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 745269.0,
      "end_time": 747637.0,
      "text": "that are analogous to aerodynamics?"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 747637.0,
      "end_time": 749391.0,
      "text": "I would argue that with technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 749391.0,
      "end_time": 751287.0,
      "text": "like the kinds I&#39;m talking about today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 751287.0,
      "end_time": 753004.0,
      "text": "maybe we can actually derive those."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 753004.0,
      "end_time": 755885.0,
      "text": "We can map the patterns that occur in living systems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 755885.0,
      "end_time": 761499.0,
      "text": "and figure out how to overcome the diseases that plague us."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 761499.0,
      "end_time": 763602.0,
      "text": "You know, my wife and I have two young kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 763602.0,
      "end_time": 766860.0,
      "text": "and one of my hopes as a bioengineer is to make life better for them"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 766860.0,
      "end_time": 768613.0,
      "text": "than it currently is for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 768613.0,
      "end_time": 772367.0,
      "text": "And my hope is, if we can turn biology and medicine"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 772367.0,
      "end_time": 776748.0,
      "text": "from these high-risk endeavors that are governed by chance and luck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 776748.0,
      "end_time": 780699.0,
      "text": "and make them things that we win by skill and hard work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 780699.0,
      "end_time": 782621.0,
      "text": "then that would be a great advance."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 782621.0,
      "end_time": 783851.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 783851.0,
      "end_time": 793851.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}